                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10967: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-10T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 10, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 10—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>562. Legation’s 556, July 9, noon. Following from American Consul General at
                    Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 9, 5 p.m. My July 8, 11 a.m. Protest was made by letter as General
                            Ho has not yet returned from Hunan.</p>
                        <pb facs="0244" n="146" xml:id="pg_146"/>
                        <p>The following telegram from Dr. Skinsnes, Sinyangchow, present head of
                            Lutheran United Mission: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>‘Suiping incident. Had no warning previous to incident. No
                                    attempt made to leave, Sandland now Kikungshan, Lee still
                                    Suiping, condition on field quiet, mission adopted no fast
                                    policy, missionaries free to follow advice and leave but adopted
                                    a watch and see policy.’”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
